description: This walk joins the Parramatta River Walk and the Great North Walk together at Bedlam Bay, with a historic stop at the Fairyland site along the way.

markers.description: Get the train to Parramatta using transportnsw.info.
From the station follow Parramatta Sq to the left.
Follow Church St to the right past the town hall.
From the town hall follow the Church St mall to Lennox Bridge.
Cross Lennox Bridge and follow the steps on the right down to the riverside.
Follow the riverside footpath towards the ferry wharf.
Get the ferry to/from Parramatta Wharf using transportnsw.info.
From the ferry wharf follow the Parramatta River Walk on the left bank of the river.
Cross Macarthur St and continue following the Parramatta River Walk.
At Morton St follow the split right.
At the Afred St Bridge keep following the Parramatta River Walk straight on.
Follow the boardwalk around the Buladarri Wetland.
At James Ruse Dr follow the path underneath the overpass.
Follow the path right along the University.
After the rail overpass follow the footpath across Vineyard Creek.
Follow Brodie St a short distance to the left along the fenceline.
At the intersection with Alan St follow the sign to the Rydalmere Ferry Wharf to the right.
From the split in the boardwalk follow the sign right to Rydalmere Ferry Wharf.
From the Thackeray St bridge follow the sign to Rydalmere Ferry Wharf straight on.
Follow the footpath right through Eric Primrose Reserve to the ferry wharf.
Get the ferry to/from Rydalmere Wharf using transportnsw.info.
There is a toilet block in the reserve near the ferry wharf.
From the ferry wharf continue on the footpath through Eric Primrose Reserve.
Follow the shared path under the Silverwater Bridge.
There is a cafe along the Ermington foreshore.
Follow the shared path through the George Kendall Riverside Park.
At the far end of the reserve follow the sign to Meadowbank right along the boardwalk.
From the end of the boardwalk follow Wharf Rd right to the board ramp.
There is a toilet block at the boat ramp.
From the boat ramp follow the footpath right from Wharf Rd.
From the end of the footpath follow Lancaster Ave to the right.
From the cover of Lancaster Ave, follow the footpath right.
Follow the shared path right along the sports fields.
Follow the path under the John Whitton Bridge to the ferry wharf.
Get the ferry to/from Meadowbank Wharf using transportnsw.info.
Get the train to/from Meadowbank Station using transportnsw.info.
There is a cafe near the ferry wharf and a shopping centre with amenities towards the strain station.
From the ferry wharf follow the riverside footpath to the right.
Follow the shared path to Ryde Bridge.
From the bridge's on ramp follow the shared path right along the riverside.
At the roundabout continue straight on along Waterview St.
Follow paths along or through Kissing Point Park to the ferry wharf.
There is a toilet block at the playground near the ferry wharf.
Get the ferry to/from Kissing Point using transportnsw.info.
From the ferry wharf follow the riverside footpath.
From the end of the footpath follow Dyson St uphill.
At the intersection follow Pellisier Rd to the right.
At Putney Park follow Jetty Rd to the left.
From the corner of Jetty Rd follow the shorefront footpath along the sports fields to the right.
Follow Teemer St to the right halfway up the sports fields.
At the intersection with Bayview St continue straight on Teemer St.
At the intersection with Kemp st continue straight on Teemer St.
At the intersection follow Tennyson Rd to the right.
At the intersection follow Brett St to the left.
Take the steps down into the park from the end of Brett St.
From the bottom of the steps follow the footpath right.
Follow the waterfront path around the Glades Bay.
Follow the boardwalk through the mangroves.
From the end of the boardwalk follow the steps up.
At the top of the steps follow the footpath through the reserve to the right.
From the end of the reserve follow Delmar Pde.
At the intersection follow the footpath left up Amiens St.
Take the steps down into the park from the end of Amiens St.
From the bottom of the steps follow the footpath left.
After the bridge across the creek follow the footpath to the right.
There is a toilet block in the picnic area.
From the picnic area follow the path along the shorefront.
From the end of the footpath follow Punt Rd to the left for a short distance.
From the right side of Punt Rd follow the trail into Bedlam Bay.
Follow the steps and boardwalks through the bushland.
From the boat shed at the end of the trail follow the footpath to the left.
After the boat shed follow the path right along the waterfront.
From the end of the sports fields follow the trail to the derelict swimming pool.
Follow the steps up from the derelict swimming pool.
From the courtyard follow the path to the left around the asylum building.
Exit the asylum compound through the front gate.
After the gate follow the footpath left through the cemetery.
At the end of the cemetery trail follow Crown Cl to the left.
Cross Crown St and follow the footpath through Gladesville Reserve.
There are public toilets in the reserve.
From the end of the reserve Follow Huntley's Point Rd to the right to the ferry wharf.
Get the ferry to/from Huntleys Point using transportnsw.info.
From roundabout at the ferry wharf follow Huntleys Point Rd to the left.
Follow the footpath underneath the Gladesville Bridge.
On the other side of the bridge follow the footpath to the left up.
From the end of Keeyuga Rd follow the footpath to the right.
Cross the Tarban Creek Bridge.
On the other side of the bridge follow the footpath up to the scout hall.
From the scout hall follow Durham St to the left.
Cross Church St at the traffic light and follow Reiby Rd downhill past the school.
From the corner of Reiby Rd follow the Great North Walk marker to the left.
From the end of Reiby Rd follow the footpath to the right underneath the Fig Tree Bridge.
Follow the footpath underneath the bridge.
From the reserve on the other side of the bridge follow the Great North Markers to the left.
From the end of the park follow Figtree Rd to the right.
At the intersection follow Ryde Rd to the right.
At the Boronia Park follow Boronia Ave to the right.
From the end of Boronia Ave follow the Great North Walk markers along the bush trail.
From the picnic shelter follow Princess St a short distance to the left.
From the right side of Princess St follow the Great North Walk sign to Newcastle.
Be mindful of the slippery creek crossing and follow the stairs on the other side.
At intersection follow the Great North Walk signs.
From the end of the boardwalk follow Pains Rd to the right.
From the right side of Pains Rd follow the Great North Walk marker.
Follow the Great North Walk markers to Buffalo Creek Reserve.
There are public toilets at the picnic area.
Find the Great North Walk trailhead to the right of the picnic area.
From the trailhead follow the boardwalk through the mangroves.
From the steps up from the mangrove boardwalk follow the Lane Cove Valley walk to the right.
At the intersection follow the Great North Walk sign to the left.
From the trailhead along Pittwater Rd follow the Great North Walk signs across the paved clearing.
Follow the boardwalk through the wetlands.
From the end of the boardwalk follow the Great North Walk sign to the right.
At the end of the trail continue along the left side of Magdala Park.
There  are public toilets at the carpark.
From the carpark follow the Great North Walk sign to Lane Cove Park
Cross the footbridge across the Lane Cove River
At the end of the path follow Epping Rd to the left.
Cross the Lane Cove River along Epping Road.
From the other side of the bridge take the steps down on the left.
Follow the footpath under the bridge.
From the other side of the bridge follow the Great North Walk sign to Fairyland.
Follow the Great North Walk markers along the Fairyland Track.
Nature reclaimed Fairyland, but the magic remains.
markers.title: Fairyland Was Here
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: From the end of the track follow Quebec Rd to the left.
From the corner of Quebec Rd follow the Great North Walk marker to the left.
From the gate at the end of the paved section, continue down the Lane Cove Valley Walk.
Follow the Great North Walk markers across the rocky sections.
From the end of the rocky section follow the Great North Walk markers down the steps.
At the bottom of the steps cross Delhi Rd and continue to the riverside on the right side of the bridge.
Follow the footpath to the left underneath the bridge.
Take the steps up on the other side of the bridge.
From the top of the steps cross the bridge over the Lane Cove River.
Cross the traffic lights on the other side and follow Fullers Road on the right.
Follow the footpath along Fullers Rd.
At the intersection continue following the footpath along Fullers Rd.
There are public toilets at Lowanna Park.
At the intersection follow the Pacific Highway to the right.
Cross the Pacific at the traffic lights or use the pedestrian bridge.
From the traffic lights follow Victoria Ave past the bus stops.
From the corner of Victoria Ave enter Chatswood Interchange. The station entrance is to the right after the underpass.
Plan your return trip from Chatswood at transportnsw.info.
